public class RequestImpl<ResultType,SOAPFaultType>
extends Object
implements Request<ResultType,SOAPFaultType>

Implementation of Request A RequestImpl, in essence, is a composition of a SOAPEnvelope for the request, a IceSoapParser for the response, and some code to to the post.

Author:
Alex Gilleran

                      Class<ResultType> resultClass,

                      SOAPRequester requester)
Creates a new request, automatically creating the parser.

Parameters:
url - The URL to post the request to
soapEnv - The SOAP envelope to send, as a SOAPEnvelope
soapAction - The SOAP Action to pass in the HTTP header - can be null
resultClass - The class of the type to return from the request.
soapFaultClass - The class of the SOAPFault that will be returned if one is encountered
requester - The implementation of SOAPRequester to use for requests.
